        {
            "_id": "dmX23IiV8D4OzC5m",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Guard Charge",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The viking guard designates an ally it can see to be its charge. The charge gains a +2 circumstance bonus to their AC, Reflex saves, and saves against fear when they are adjacent to the viking guard. Further, this allows the viking guard to use its Sacrifice and Shield Wall actions. A viking guard can have only one charge at a time, and if it designates a new charge, the old one loses all benefits. If the viking guard's charge is reduced to 0 Hit Points, the viking guard must succeed at a @Check[will|dc:30] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2}; this is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Guard Charge]</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
